INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A network engineer needs to programmatically modify the configuration of a Cisco IOS-XE device using a standards-based protocol that operates over SSH on port 830 and uses XML-encoded YANG data models. Which protocol best meets these requirements?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"RESTCONF over HTTPS"},{"id":"b","text":"NETCONF over SSH"},{"id":"c","text":"gRPC with Protocol Buffers"},{"id":"d","text":"REST API with JSON payloads"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material states: 'NETCONF (RFC 6241): XML-based, runs over SSH (port 830), uses YANG models.' This precisely matches all three requirements — SSH transport, port 830, and XML-encoded YANG data. RESTCONF (option A) uses HTTPS, not SSH on port 830, and while it also leverages YANG, it wraps operations over HTTP. gRPC (option C) uses Protocol Buffers and is primarily used for streaming telemetry, not standard configuration management via SSH/830. REST with JSON (option D) is stateless and HTTP-based, with no native YANG or SSH-on-830 transport.$patch$, $patch$Automation$patch$,
         4, $json$[{"url":"https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc6241","label":"RFC 6241 – Network Configuration Protocol (NETCONF)"},{"url":"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/ios-xml/ios/prog/configuration/1612/b_1612_programmability_cg/configuring_yang_datamodel.html","label":"Cisco IOS XE NETCONF/YANG Configuration Guide"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
