INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A Python developer is writing a script to retrieve interface statistics from a Cisco device's REST API. The script receives an HTTP response code of 403. What is the correct interpretation of this status code, and what should the developer investigate first?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The request succeeded but returned an empty body; investigate the payload parsing logic."},{"id":"b","text":"The server encountered an internal error; retry the request after a delay."},{"id":"c","text":"The client sent an invalid request syntax; check the URL formatting."},{"id":"d","text":"The client is authenticated but lacks permission for the resource; investigate authorization credentials or roles."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["d"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material groups HTTP status codes as follows: '2xx success, 3xx redirect, 4xx client error, 5xx server error.' A 403 Forbidden is a 4xx client error indicating the client is authenticated but not authorized to access the requested resource — the server understood the request but refuses to fulfill it. The developer should investigate the user's role, token scope, or OAuth permissions, not syntax (400 Bad Request would indicate that). Option B describes a 5xx server-side error. Option A describes a 2xx scenario. Option C describes a 400 Bad Request scenario.$patch$, $patch$Automation$patch$,
         4, $json$[{"url":"https://developer.cisco.com/learning/tracks/devnet-express-network-fund/networking-basics/dnav3-101/step/1","label":"Cisco DevNet – REST API Fundamentals"},{"url":"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Status/403","label":"MDN Web Docs – HTTP Response Status Codes"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
