INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A large financial institution needs to extend encrypted group communications across its existing private MPLS WAN. The solution must preserve IP multicast traffic without requiring spoke-to-spoke tunnels and must use a group keying model rather than pairwise SA negotiations. Which Cisco VPN technology best meets these requirements?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"DMVPN Phase 3 with IPsec profiles"},{"id":"b","text":"AnyConnect SSL VPN with split tunneling"},{"id":"c","text":"GETVPN (Group Encrypted Transport VPN)"},{"id":"d","text":"IKEv2 FlexVPN with virtual tunnel interfaces"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material states: 'GETVPN (Group Encrypted Transport): for private MPLS, preserves multicast.' GETVPN is uniquely designed for private WAN environments (such as MPLS) where a full-mesh overlay tunnel model is unnecessary. It uses a group key management model — a Key Server distributes a common Group Security Association (GSA) to all Group Members — so any site can decrypt traffic from any other site without pairwise SA negotiation. Critically, GETVPN performs tunnel-less encryption that preserves the original IP header, allowing native multicast routing to function end-to-end. DMVPN is appropriate for hub-and-spoke or dynamic mesh topologies over public internet but requires GRE tunnels and does not natively preserve multicast across the WAN fabric in the same way. AnyConnect is a remote-access solution and is irrelevant to site-to-site WAN encryption. IKEv2 FlexVPN is a flexible point-to-point or hub-and-spoke IPsec solution but still requires tunnel interfaces and pairwise SAs, and does not offer the group key model of GETVPN.$patch$, $patch$Security$patch$,
         4, $json$[{"url":"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/solutions/Enterprise/WAN_and_MAN/GETVPN/GETVPN_DIG.html","label":"Cisco: Group Encrypted Transport VPN (GETVPN) Design and Implementation Guide"},{"url":"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/docs/security-vpn/ipsec-negotiation-ike-protocols/116091-technote-getvpn-00.html","label":"Cisco: GETVPN vs DMVPN Technology Comparison"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = '350-401-P2'
