INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A network engineer is writing a Python script to retrieve interface statistics from a Cisco IOS XE device using NETCONF. The script successfully establishes a session but must target the correct TCP port and transport protocol. Which port and transport does NETCONF use according to RFC 6241?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"TCP port 443 over HTTPS"},{"id":"b","text":"TCP port 830 over SSH"},{"id":"c","text":"TCP port 161 over UDP"},{"id":"d","text":"TCP port 8080 over HTTP"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$According to the source material: 'NETCONF (RFC 6241): XML-based, runs over SSH (port 830), uses YANG models.' NETCONF mandates SSH as its mandatory-to-implement transport and IANA has assigned port 830 for this purpose. Option (a) describes RESTCONF, which uses HTTPS (port 443). Option (c) describes SNMP's transport, which uses UDP port 161. Option (d) describes a generic HTTP alternate port not associated with NETCONF.$patch$, $patch$Automation$patch$,
         4, $json$[{"url":"https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc6241","label":"RFC 6241 – Network Configuration Protocol (NETCONF)"},{"url":"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/ios-xml/ios/prog/configuration/1612/b_1612_programmability_cg/netconf_protocol.html","label":"Cisco IOS XE Programmability Configuration Guide – NETCONF Protocol"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = '350-401-P2'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A network engineer is writing a Python script to retrieve interface statistics from a Cisco IOS XE device using NETCONF. The script successfully establishes a session but must target the correct TCP port and transport protocol. Which port and transport does NETCONF use according to RFC 6241?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A network automation engineer must choose a configuration management tool that is agentless and uses YAML-based playbooks to push configuration changes to Cisco IOS devices via SSH. The engineer also requires a module specifically designed for IOS device configuration. Which tool and module combination best satisfies these requirements?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Puppet using a Ruby DSL manifest with the cisco_ios resource type"},{"id":"b","text":"Chef using a Ruby DSL cookbook with the ios_template recipe"},{"id":"c","text":"Ansible using YAML playbooks with the ios_config module"},{"id":"d","text":"Terraform using a declarative HCL file with a Cisco provider resource"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material states: 'Ansible: agentless, YAML playbooks, SSH/NETCONF. Modules like ios_config, nxos_config.' Ansible requires no agent on managed devices and communicates over SSH, making it the only option that is both agentless and YAML-based. Option (a) Puppet and option (b) Chef are described in the source as 'agent-based, Ruby DSL,' disqualifying them on both the agentless and YAML requirements. Option (d) Terraform is a declarative infrastructure-as-code tool using HCL (HashiCorp Configuration Language) and maintains a state file; it is not a YAML-playbook-driven, SSH-native IOS configuration tool. The ios_config Ansible module sends IOS CLI commands or configuration blocks directly to Cisco devices over SSH, fulfilling the stated requirements.$patch$, $patch$Automation$patch$,
         4, $json$[{"url":"https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/collections/cisco/ios/ios_config_module.html","label":"Ansible Documentation – cisco.ios.ios_config module"},{"url":"https://developer.cisco.com/automation-ansible/","label":"Cisco DevNet – Network Automation with Ansible"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = '350-401-P2'
